This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it focuses on convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and their ability to efficiently process sparse data. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of attention mechanisms, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks. 

The paper also discusses the adaptation of the back-propagation algorithm, which is a common learning framework used in machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). 

The use of sparsity in both the feature maps and filter weights is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data science (cs.DS) to reduce memory footprints and computation times. 

Overall, the most likely sub-categories for this paper are cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, and cs.DS.
